I did a lot more than that but here's a crack at it.\

Lodge of the Travelers- Magic involving the movement, transport and discovery of new places. They do things as minor as levitation and as major as constructing permanent magical portal gates. High end transportation spells and Communication like having magic satellite internet. More the prankster wizard as they out and about and don't hold contempt for "uninitiated"

House of the Shapers- Magic focusing on the creation of, and modification of inanimate things. Much more than just transmutation, like they could go up to a cast iron pipe and give it the same structural and chemical makeup of forged steel. They can also apply spells of self mending, allowing given objects to self repair from certain things. They can pull elements from the earth if needed.

The Enchanter's Way: Specialize in enchantments of a more magical sort. Like a refrigerated barrel or self-igniting sword, but also sets of books that all share the same written words as they appear. They also make material from magic itself, which can be rather useful for those who know to use it.

Warrior's Host. Battle Wizards and Warlocks, unlike usual explosive fireballs or chain lighting these wizards can also grant boons to entire armies, and summon far more powerful spells including beyond line of sight combat spells. They can do some minor summoning but most relates to combat spells and buffing spells.

The Gardeners
These wizards focus on the natural magic, while they're most powerful over plants, able to raise entire fields from seed to the stalk in a moment or twist a living tree into a home. More so they can increase the effectiveness of herbs and turn dying plants into a sort of plant golem, but it has agency.

The Good Samaritans
These men are healers, helpers, and wisdom speakers, they live lives unlike their peers using their magic to aid one community, but have hidden meetings.

The Summoners
Deal with other planes, and its kin
